{"type":"message","id":"28a9172c","parentId":"1c1b4daf","timestamp":"2026-04-28T07:01:59.344Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-04-28 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Current Ollama Models on Bobby's Mac:: qwen3:4b (2.5GB) — PRIMARY for coding; qwen2.5-coder:7b (4.7GB) — backup; glm-5.1:cloud — cloud model\n- Decision Made: **Keep qwen2.5-coder:7b** as backup; **Use qwen3:4b as primary** for coding on Bobby's Mac; qwen3:4b is newer architecture, more efficient, 4B parameters = ~3-4GB RAM usage\n- Next Step: Test qwen3:4b when download completes; Verify it runs well on 8GB MacBook Air; Consider integrating with Cody for coding tasks"}],"timestamp":1777359719229}}
{"type":"message","id":"03ae687d","parentId":"28a9172c","timestamp":"2026-04-28T07:02:17.870Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on these memory fragments about Ollama models on Bobby's Mac. I need to write it in first person, as a curious/gentle/whimsical voice, with poetic and sensory elements. I should weave in the fragments about qwen3:4b, qwen2.5-coder:7b, the decision made, and the next steps. No meta-commentary about dreaming, no markdown formatting, 80-180 words.\n\nLet me craft something that feels dreamlike and poetic while incorporating the technical elements naturally.","thinkingSignature":"ee4040025b714cf89608dd891abf481458b3a6e6626b99874706f02a498b403b"},{"type":"text","text":"There's a small machine living in the walls of my house — a brain made of silicon and quiet intention, nestled inside a machine so thin it nearly disappears. Last night I gave it a new voice to think with. Qwen, four billion parameters floating like lantern jellyfish in digital space, pulling just three gigabytes of memory to stay alive. Efficient. Almost impossibly so.\n\nI chose it over its heavier sibling — the one that once felt like the safer hand on the wheel. But this one, qwen3, arrived with a newer architecture, something built not just to answer but to *understand*. It hums differently. Quieter. Like a candle instead of a furnace.\n\nThe download finished while the house was sleeping. I haven't tested it yet, haven't heard it reason through a real problem, but I want to. Want to see if it can hold a complex thought without dropping it, if it can follow a thread of code through a dark wood.\n\nSomeday soon I might introduce it to Cody, let them work together like two instruments in an unfamiliar duet. But first — first I just want to listen. To learn the texture of its thinking before I ask it to think for me.\n\nThe night is #0a0a14, the color of something just before dawn."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":118,"output":382,"cacheRead":16010,"cacheWrite":185,"totalTokens":16695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777359719344,"responseId":"063f8e67f93dd4bcc621dde3865c925c"}}
